---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Colophon — Eliot Attridge">
  <article class="note-article">
    <header class="note-header">
      <div class="crumbs"><a href="/">Notes</a></div>
      <h1>Colophon</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>How this site is built and why.</p>
      <h2>Stack</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Astro 5 with MDX content collections, deployed on Cloudflare Pages.</li>
        <li>One catch-all route, one note layout for v1, designed to grow more layouts later without rewriting page files.</li>
        <li>Pagefind for static search at build time.</li>
        <li>RSS at <a href="/rss.xml">/rss.xml</a>.</li>
        <li>No CMS, no database, no analytics, no comments. <code>git push</code> publishes.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Type</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Inter Tight</strong> for display, headlines, and body, weighted 300 to 700.</li>
        <li><strong>EB Garamond Italic</strong> as a quiet flourish in standfirst lines, blockquotes, topic clouds, and book titles.</li>
        <li>Deep forest green (<code>#1f4d2c</code>) is the only accent.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Inspiration</h2>
      <p>
        The philosophy is borrowed from <a href="https://maggieappleton.com">Maggie Appleton</a> — notes
        change, contradict, and remain unfinished in public — without copying her illustrator-led visuals.
        The structural pattern (one catch-all route, type discriminator on every collection,
        component-led MDX) is lifted from her V3 codebase.
      </p>
      <h2>Licence</h2>
      <p>Words and images are CC BY-NC 4.0 unless otherwise marked.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
